names.fullName: The crystal structure of yeast protein disulfide isomerase suggests cooperativity between its active sites.

attributeList.attribute: Tian G., Xiang S., Noiva R., Lennarz WJ., Schindelin H.

The structure looks like an 'U' with the a and a prime being the top of the letter U and the bend of the U being the regions b and b prime. The dimensions are 80A for width and 60A for height. Each of the a, a prime, b and b prime adopt a thioredoxin fold. In the crystal the b domain of a symmetry-related molecule extensively interacts with the a domain.
Four PDI molecules form a tetramer around a crystallographic 4-fold axis of symmetry.
